3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for improving the performance of a given model purely at test time without any further training steps, which is a common goal in the field of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the application of uncertainty modeling to convolutional neural networks, which falls under the domain of neural computing. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although the paper does not explicitly focus on natural language processing, the proposed method could potentially be applied to tasks such as sentiment analysis or text classification, which fall under the domain of computation and language.
